<font size="1">Genoli Whitewolf, Terris Thule</i></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FDF8DB><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usalbianbb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SalbianBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/30/01 7:36:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about foraging Epic items</span><hr size=1> I have 200 forage and it took me about 30min in Misty. 10 min in everfrost.30 min in G Fay and the longest was Innothule Swamp with 1 1/2 hour.I think your forage needs to be higher and certainly will not hurt. If you have the points and money train it up.<br>
<br>
Salbian<br>
59 Preserver of Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqueylawindrider.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Queyla Windrider</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/30/01 7:47:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You're doing it right.</span><hr size=1> Well, I've completed this part of the epic and 130 is SOMEWHAT relevant.<br>
<br>
But now I'm putting the forage skills to the test again on the Tunarean Signet Ring quest.<br>
<br>
3 hours in Gfay click click click.  No Item yet level 57 with 200 forage.<br>
<br>
Queyla Beefcake<br>
Havenlight Applicant<br>
Norrath Lands Of Xegony <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uanicorepeacewolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anicore PeaceWolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/30/01 5:31:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.bestanimations.com/Computers/Folder-01.gif HEIGHT=87 WIDTH=51></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You're doing it right.</span><hr size=1> No, if you go to a certain spot you won't be able to forage the mudroot.  You will get the mudroot about 1/100 (maybe 200?) if your forage is MAXED (200 skill) at about 130 it would probably be 1/500.  Somewhere around there.  What I did to get it maxed was I always clicked the forage button when it was free.  That way when I port ppl I give them free food/drink and my forage skill gets better.  I have many ppl that supply me with money for the foraging skill.  So you could make money doing this skill without any cost.  It also helps for this part of the epic.  I suggest you put the forage button on the first little macros sheet (the one you see at the bottom left of your screen)    It only took me an hour at maxxed skill.  The avg is about an hour and a half...From what my friends told me.  Keep up the foraging, and I hope this helped *hugs* =) <p>Anicore PeaceWolf 
Of the 53rd Season
The Final Covenant
My <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18923" </A> Profile</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugavick.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gavick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 5:26:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You're doing it right.</span><hr size=1> The higher your skill in foraging the better.  And it needs to be at least 100.  Specific spots in a zone don't affect your chances, not to my knowledge anyhow.<br>
<br>
I too am trying the Tunarean signet foraging.  But stuff in Gfay and BB that I have foraged a hundred times in the past, now eludes me.  /sigh<br>
